<node TEXT="There are about 60 species of Arctostaphylos, ranging from ground-hugging arctic, coastal, and mountain species to small trees up to 6 m tall. Most are evergreen (one species deciduous), with small oval leaves 1&#x2013;7 cm long, arranged spirally on the stems. The flowers are bell-shaped, white or pale pink, and borne in small clusters of 2-20 together; flowering is in the spring. The fruit are small berries, ripening in the summer or autumn. The berries of some species are edible." ID="ID_11736088" CREATED="1432386100827" MODIFIED="1432386121031"/>
<node TEXT="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Arctostaphylos" ID="ID_716773499" CREATED="1432386181351" MODIFIED="1432386181351" LINK="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Arctostaphylos"/>
