<node TEXT="Yardlong Bean &#x201c;They&#x2019;re not incredibly exotic, but their pods can grow to lengths of two feet or more,&#x201d; Grant says of this popular bean in Southeast Asian cuisine. &#x201c;They look like noodles.&#x201d; Grow these fun veggies on trellises to give the pods room to hang. For fresh bean flavor, harvest before the seeds start to swell. Or wait for the pods to dry out to harvest beans that taste much like black-eyed peas. &#x201c;Yardlong beans do incredibly well here in the Midwest,&#x201d; Grant says. &#x201c;Try &#x2018;Chinese Red Noodle&#x2019; and &#x2018;Chinese Green Noodle&#x2019; varieties that are very similar but with different colored pods.&#x201d;" ID="ID_1745631055" CREATED="1423377401396" MODIFIED="1423377404816"/>
