<node TEXT="Lagochilus is a genus of 34 species in the Lamiaceae, native to central Asia. They are subshrubs to 2 feet with white to pink flowers. The herb is used medicinally as a styptic, hypotensive, sedative and adaptogenic. Studies in Russia showed that the plant extract improved resistance to hypothermia in an ice bath test. Turkestan mint&#x2019;s use as a styptic is due to its Vitamin K content, and tannins." ID="ID_997941753" CREATED="1432389668904" MODIFIED="1432389678868"/>
<node TEXT="Good drainage is important&#xa;Turkestan mint requires full sun&#xa;The plant grows on rocky slopes, in poor dry soils" ID="ID_391033794" CREATED="1432389679424" MODIFIED="1432389680620"/>
</node>
