<node TEXT="Vitex is a genus of approximately 24 species of shrubs and small trees formerly in the Verbenaceae, but now transferred to the Lamiaceae. They are cultivated as ornamentals due to their display of flowers in spring, and some provide valuable timber, particularly the African species. Many are used medicinally, and some of the African species produce edible fruits, known as &#x201c;chocolate berries&#x201d;." ID="ID_378423526" CREATED="1432400420071" MODIFIED="1432400421977"/>
<node TEXT="Most plants withstand some drought&#xa;Vitex species occur from temperate to tropical conditions in a wide range of habitats" ID="ID_1898947663" CREATED="1432400432377" MODIFIED="1432400435723"/>
</node>
</node>
