<node TEXT="Celtis is a genus of approximately 70 species of deciduous trees variously placed in the Ulmaceae, Celtidaceae, or Cannabaceae. The plants are native to warm temperate regions of the Northern Hemisphere, with a few found in south Africa and South America. They range in size from 30 to 80 feet in height. The edible fruits are small drupes &#xbc; to &#x2153; inches in diameter, with a dry sugary flesh." ID="ID_1311034372" CREATED="1432393332252" MODIFIED="1432393343328"/>
<node TEXT="The trees are drought tolerant once established&#xa;They are occasionally subject to fungal diseases&#xa;The larvae of certain Lepidoptera feed on the leaves&#xa;They are important sources of wildlife food, and the flowers are good bee pasture" ID="ID_337741397" CREATED="1432393343886" MODIFIED="1432393345088"/>
</node>
