<node TEXT="Hippophae is a genus of 7 species in the Elaeagnaceae, native to Eurasia. They are much-branched shrubs to 20 feet in height. The dioecious plants have grey-green foliage and woody spines along the branches. The brown flowers are wind pollinated, and are followed by orange berries in dense clusters along the branches. The fruit are high in Vitamins C, E, oils, and polyphenols." ID="ID_784716591" CREATED="1432390123412" MODIFIED="1432390136780"/>
<node TEXT="The plants fix nitrogen and are soil improvers&#xa;They tolerate dry winds, drought, cold, and saline soils&#xa;In the former Soviet bloc countries, many improved varieties have been developed" ID="ID_1769332965" CREATED="1432390137225" MODIFIED="1432390138630"/>
