<node TEXT="Lycium is a genus of approximately 70 species of shrubs in the Solanaceae, mainly found in drier parts of North and South America, southern Africa, and Asia. They are shrubs from 3 to 10 feet, with thick leaves adapted to store moisture. The plants are often thorny; L. ferocissimum is grown around villages in Africa to repel lions. The fruits are high in carotenoids, and the young leaves are edible." ID="ID_414254700" CREATED="1432394524121" MODIFIED="1432394526794"/>
