<node TEXT=" Since tomatoes produce a fruit, they&apos;ll need fertilizing that is low in nitrogen, high in phosphorous and medium to high levels of potassium. Ph level of the soil should be around 6.2 to 6.8. Fish emulsion diluted with lots of water is good for foliage, which in turn supports root and fruit growth, and compost tea and manure tea are good. Crushed eggshells help when you plant your seedlings. If plants are over fertilized, you&apos;ll get lots of leaves and little fruit, so there is a balance point between too much fertilizer and too little. Since I don&apos;t know what kind of soil you have, it&apos;s hard to tell. Your plants look lovely, by the way!" ID="ID_98532728" CREATED="1382812047857" MODIFIED="1382812076731"/>
